For Halcyon I won't advice to put too much money inside this company as you can see their short term asset doesn't cover their short term liabilities which then will turn into debts and looking at Halcyon Debt to Equity Ratio you can see the Equity dropping but debt increasing.. This means that they have negative cash flow and even though their revenue has increased over the year the reason why their profits are not increasing also its because a good portion of the revenue goes to pay their debts and liabilities..I prefer ppl invest into a company where insider holds at least a Quarter of their shareholdings  because when the management has a big portion of their pay they will make sure they cook & prepare it properly.And I don't see much BB involvement in their businessAs compared to Sri Trang Agro  both their long term and short term asset can cover their liabilities which means their debt should be decreasing if revenue goes up profit will go up as well. And take a look at their top 20 shareholders
